page.title: 09Rare Birds in Sarn 1
page.content: Mr Pritchard has a building behind the school where he keeps about 80 birds.He has thirteen different sorts of rare birds.Here are some of them: Zebra Finches,Cockateal,Peach- faced Love Birds,Kakarikies,Golden Mantle Rosella,Red Rumps and Splendid Parrakeets.The rarest pair he has is the Kakarikies.He sells some of his birds for pets,and others to pet shops in{Shrewsbury.}Each bird eats about 14lb a week.The food eaten is canary seed,millet seed,sunflower seed,hemp seed,millet spray,panicum millet, peanuts,apples,oranges and grapes.The female birds lay about 5 eggs each.The eggs take about 14 days to hatch out. He takes his birds to Oswestry Show.He does not have his birds insured because it would cost too much money.
